As we continue to evolve and strengthen our ecosystem, a new, community-driven initiative beckons — one that is crucial for our advancement towards a more decentralized and self-sustaining future.

Historically, Divi Labs has played a central role in funding market making activities, ensuring the liquidity and stability of our coin. In alignment with our commitment to decentralization, it is time for this mantle to be passed to the community. This shift represents a significant step towards greater autonomy and a testament to our collective strength and maturity as a decentralized project.
To facilitate this transition smoothly, we have outlined several funding options, offering flexibility and catering to our diverse community:
3 Months: 9,800 USDT (Discounted Price for Divi Payment)
6 Months: 16,000 USDT (Discounted Price for Divi Payment)
12 Months: 24,000 USDT (Discounted Price for Divi Payment)
These options provide us with the agility to choose a plan that best suits our immediate needs while allowing for future adjustments based on our collective experience and insights.

In a show of continued support and commitment, Divi Labs has agreed to leave the currently allocated liquidity in the exchange. This gesture not only demonstrates their confidence in our ability to lead this initiative but also ensures we have substantial ‘skin in the game’ as we undertake this important transition.

By participating in this funding effort, you are not just supporting the operational aspect of market making. You are actively contributing to a fundamental pillar of our project’s ethos — decentralization and community empowerment. Your involvement signifies a shared belief in the strength and potential of our collective efforts.
This is more than a funding proposal
column2: it’s a call to action for all of us to play a pivotal role in the next chapter of Divi’s story. Together, we can ensure a stable, vibrant, and self-governed ecosystem that stands as a testament to what a united community can achieve.

Divi project, the blockchain, like other projects, had an ICO. In this ICO it collected a little over $2M, with a whitepaper you can still find online.
Overall. this whitepaper has been achieved, and more. However, $2M were definitely not enough to cover those costs.

You will see that not a lot of projects of 2017 are still alive today.

To be able to survive, projects like Divi have to find private investors to develop tech. They need to be incentivized by the revenue potential or the growth it can bring to be attracted by the investment.
Divi labs has been critical for Divi the blockchain to remain alive during the last few years, funding critical services through private investment, the laliga deal.

Hey @DiviEspaña ! MM is market making. the short version is a third party providing services with their proprietary bots to generate volume and provide liquidity on exchanges.

A market maker or liquidity provider is a company or an individual that quotes both a buy and a sell price in a tradable asset held in inventory, hoping to make a profit on the bid–ask spread, or turn. The benefit to the firm is that it makes money from doing so
